JENNIE, THE OLD DRUM HORSE of the 7th Dragoon Guards, was the only one to survive, of the black horses on which the Regiment was mounted at the commencement of the S.A. Campaign. After the campaign every officer N.C.O. and man in the Regt was so proud of the commanding officer obtained permission to purchase her from the Goverment out of the Regiment Funds. She thus became the property of the Regiment and was the Regiment pet. On the return of the 7th Dn Guards to Englands in August 1904, they bought her with them. She always carried the drums from November 1902 until she arrived to England, after the time she only carried them on special occasions. She died in August 1905, from enteritis, caused by the sand which caused into the system in Africa. Up until the time of her death, she was trained to march at the head of the band without a rider and was making great progress.
